    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>In a class, the ratio of students who wear glasses to those who don&#x2019;t is 3 to 5. If there are 32 students in the class, how many students wear glasses? Show your reasoning.</p>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>12 students. Sample reasoning: The total number of parts in the ratio is 8. <span class="math math-repaired">\(32 \div 8 = 4\)</span>, so each part represents 4 students, and <span class="math math-repaired">\(3 \boldcdot 4 = 12\)</span>.</p>

<p><img src="/tikz_files/205235.svg" /></p>
